CHANGES
=======

Unreleased (2026-03-07)
-----------------------

* move the GitHub CLI workflow npm auth token to job scope so the publish step inherits the same registry credentials used earlier in the run instead of overriding them with an empty step-local value.
* allow the GitHub CLI workflow to publish and create the GitHub release when manually dispatched on an existing CLI tag, so a failed tagged release can be retried without minting a new version.
* add package-local `release:preflight` support so a single package can run cleanbuild, tests, and local release checks from its own directory.
* stop using `setup-node` pnpm caching in the GitHub CLI release workflow because this repo does not ship a `pnpm-lock.yaml`.
* install workspace dependencies with `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile --link-workspace-packages` in the GitHub CLI release workflow because this repo does not ship a `pnpm-lock.yaml` and the CLI depends on the local prerelease client package.
* add a repo-level pnpm build-script allowlist for `sqlite3` and `esbuild`, while explicitly blocking `@scarf/scarf`, so clean GitHub installs can run the shared test/build pipeline before publishing the CLI.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

v2.0.0-beta1 (2026-03-07)
-------------------------

* stage the `2.0.0-beta1` prerelease and align package metadata with it.
* add a GitHub Actions CLI release workflow that verifies, packs, publishes to npm on tag pushes, and creates a GitHub Release.
* replace the internal `workspace:*` client dependency with a publishable `^2.0.0-beta1` range and add a `files` whitelist for the public CLI tarball.
* add shared local/CI release verification tooling plus a local `npm publish --dry-run` path so package publication can be smoke-tested before tagging.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

v1.0.4 (2026-03-06)
-------------------

* add `mm-cli reload` command to trigger a server-side force-reload via the API.
* preserve newer form config fields and patch returned `form_key` values even when a form inherits locale from the domain default.
* add regression coverage for form field round-tripping and inherited-locale `--patch-source-ids` write-back.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

v1.0.3 (2026-03-05)
-------------------

* parse `--part false` correctly instead of treating any non-empty string as truthy.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Claude Code (profile: anthropic-claude-opus-4-6/high).)

v1.0.2 (2026-03-04)
-------------------

* correctly preserve child block overrides across multi-level `{% extends %}` chains during template merge.
* add regression coverage for three-level template inheritance to prevent override loss.
* reject absolute/traversing template `filename` values from `init-data.json` when resolving tx/form template paths.
* add regression coverage for rejecting unsafe `filename` path traversal during `compileConfigTree`.
* add opt-in `MMCLI_ALLOW_UNSAFE_TEMPLATE_PATHS` env flag for legacy imports that depend on absolute or traversing template `filename` values.
* support natural-key domain mapping (`domain` name) in config records for compile/push flows; treat numeric `domain_id` as optional hints.
* add `push-dir` write-back controls (`--patch-source-ids`, `--backup`) for opt-in source mutation of resolved IDs/keys.
* add opt-in source patching of resolved `form_key` values back into `init-data.json`.
* remove local `push-dir` lock/state file handling (`.mail-magic-sync.json`) to avoid a false sense of cross-process safety.
* document `MMCLI_ALLOW_UNSAFE_TEMPLATE_PATHS` in `.mmcli-env` settings.
* document `push-dir` write-back flags and natural-key domain mapping support.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: chatgpt-5.3-codex/medium).)

v1.0.1 (2026-02-22)
-------------------

* add package-level `release:check` script and wire `release` to shared publish script.
* replace `rm -rf` cleanup scripts with `rimraf`.
* quiet package test output by default (silent Vitest + silent shared-sync step).
* add a compile smoke test that compiles `packages/server/examples/data` via `compileConfigTree`.
* defer `loadCliEnv()` from module load time to just before `program.parse()`, preventing file-system side effects when the module is imported at startup; apply env-file defaults via `setOptionValueWithSource` so CLI flags still override them correctly.
* document the `version` command, the `--css` parameter for `compile`/`push`/`push-dir`, and the `--skip-tx`/`--skip-forms` flags for `push-dir`.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Claude Code (profile: anthropic-claude-sonnet-4-6/high).)
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: chatgpt-5.3-codex/medium).)

v1.0.0 (2026-02-22)
-------------------

* add package CHANGES file in required format.
* (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: chatgpt-5.3-codex/medium).)
